# generated/assembled artifacts (the template ships sources, not outputs)
*.zip
.harness/handoffs/
# self-update remote (a user's private repo URL — keep it out of the tracked tree)
.harness/remote
# per-machine agent permissions, written by the tool as you work. The tracked
# presets are config/settings.local.*.json.example — this is somebody's local copy.
.claude/settings.local.json

# This project's OWN working records — kept local, never published. They are about whoever runs
# this harness (names, decisions, costs, session history), and this repo ships to other people.
# They are NOT deleted: they live on disk and are research that must not be thrown away (R9).
# scripts/leak-gate.sh enforces the other half — no operator's name in anything tracked.
#
# NOTE: what USERS get is unaffected. setup.sh scaffolds a .planning/ and a docs/feedback/ in
# THEIR project (from templates/ and docs/feedback/README.md, both still tracked) — these two
# lines only stop this repo from publishing its own.
.planning/
docs/feedback/[0-9]*.md
